-- Spanish Bonds Stay Lower as Draghi Speaks on Economy, Inflation
-- B y   L u c y   M e a k i n
-- 2013-06-06T12:44:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-06/spanish-bonds-stay-lower-as-draghi-speaks-on-economy-inflation.html
Spanish and Italian bonds stayed
lower after European Central Bank President  Mario Draghi  said
policy makers cut their 2013 growth and inflation forecasts.  Spain’s 10-year  yield  rose two basis points to 4.46 percent
at 1:42 p.m. London time. Italy’s increased three basis points
to 4.16 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lucy Meakin in London at 
